2.name: Accompanying goods
2.desc: Notice that a specific document will be accompanying the goods.

3.name: Conditionally accepted
3.desc: The specified document is conditionally accepted.

4.name: To arrive by separate EDI message
4.desc:
Notice that a specific document/message will be transmitted via a
                                    separate EDI message.

5.name: Information only
5.desc: Notice that the specific document or message is for information only.

6.name: To arrive by manual means
6.desc: Notice that a specific document or message will not be sent via EDI.

7.name: To be raised and sent
7.desc:
Request for a specific message to be formatted and transmitted or a
                                    request for a specific document to be raised and sent.

9.name: To be printed
9.desc: The document or message is to be printed.

12.name: Document exhausted by declaration and attached
12.desc:
Customs declaration to which the document is related completed or
                                    exhaust the allowance stated on the document. The document is attached to the
                                    Customs declaration.

13.name: Document not exhausted by declaration and attached
13.desc:
Customs declaration to which the document is related does not complete
                                    or exhaust the allowance stated on the document . The document is not attached to
                                    the declaration but has already been lodged in the Customs station.

14.name: Document exhausted by declaration and previously lodged
14.desc:
Customs declaration to which the document is related completed or
                                    exhaust the allowance stated on the document. The usage of the document is complete.
                                    The document is not attached to the declaration but has already been lodged in the
                                    Customs station.

15.name: Document not exhausted by declaration and previously lodged
15.desc:
Customs declaration to which the document is related does not complete
                                    or exhaust the allowance stated on the document. The document can continue to be
                                    used for future declarations until the allowance is exhausted. The document is not
                                    attached to the declaration but has already been lodged in the Customs station.

16.name: Document not attached
16.desc: Specified document is not or cannot be attached.

17.name: Document with the goods
17.desc:
Document not attached to the Customs declaration but is attached to
                                    the goods.

18.name: Document attached, to be returned after endorsement
18.desc:
Specified document is attached to the Customs declaration and will be
                                    required to be returned to the declarant after Customs endorsement.

19.name: Document applied for
19.desc: Application has been submitted for that document.

20.name: Received for shipment
20.desc:
Indicates that the document has legal validity from the date of
                                    receival of the cargo.

21.name: Shipped on board
21.desc:
Indicates that the document has legal validity from the date that
                                    cargo is loaded on board a vessel.

26.name: Document not freighted
26.desc: Document not to include freight figures.

28.name: Archived
28.desc: The document or message has been archived.

29.name: Provisional
29.desc: The document or message has no official status.

30.name: Documents enclosed in the first transmission
30.desc: The documents are enclosed in the first transmission.

31.name: Documents enclosed in the second transmission
31.desc: The documents are enclosed in the second transmission.

32.name: Document not required, waiver issued
32.desc: The document is not required, waiver of requirement has been issued.

33.name: Already on file with receiver of this message
33.desc: The document is already on file with the party receiving the message.

34.name:
Retained by sender of this message, or by sender's agent or
                                    representative
34.desc:
The document is in the possession of the sender or sender's agent or
                                    representative.

36.name: Document previously submitted
36.desc: The document has already been submitted.
